addCustomData

void addCustomData(Field field,
                   Object values)
                   throws SedException,
                          SedNoDataException,
                          SedNullException,
                          SedInconsistentException
Creates new data custom data parameters to each point for a given field. The field id is used to determine which parameter should be added/changed If the point already has a data parameter with the given id, parameter information will be replaced by the new information.

Parameters:
field - Field
values - Object
Throws:
SedException, - SedNoDataException, SedNullException, SedInconsistentException

getCustomDataValues

Object getCustomDataValues(String id)
                           throws SedNoDataException,
                                  SedNullException
Gets the values of the specified custom data id. If no data exists a SedException will be thrown. For points where the axis is not set a default value is used; for doubles its NaN for ints its -9999 and empty strings for strings.

Parameters:
id - String
Returns:
either null or double[] or int[] depending on the data. The arrays will be cast to an Object.
Throws:
SedNoDataException, - SedNullException
SedNoDataException
SedNullException

setCustomDataInfo

void setCustomDataInfo(Field field)
                       throws SedNoDataException,
                              SedNullException
Sets the parameter info of the specified custom parameters. The field id is used to determine which parameter should be changed. The specified field will replace all information on each point except for the value. If no data exists for the specified id on a particular point the point will be ignored. Creates new data custom data parameters to each point for a given field id. If the point already has a data parameter with the given id, parameter information will be replaced by the new information.

Parameters:
field - Field
Throws:
SedNoDataException, - SedNullException
SedNoDataException
SedNullException

setCustomDataValues

void setCustomDataValues(String id,
                         Object values)
                         throws SedNoDataException,
                                SedInconsistentException,
                                SedNullException
Sets the values of the custom data id. The first n values of the are set in the spectral axis. If the array is larger then the number of points, then the extra values are ignored.

Parameters:
values - Valid values are double[], float[], int[], short[], long[] or String[]
Throws:
SedNoDataException, - SedInconsistentException, SedNullException
SedNoDataException
SedInconsistentException
SedNullException

setDataInfo

void setDataInfo(Field field,
                 String utype)
                 throws SedInconsistentException,
                        SedNoDataException
Sets the parameter info of the specified axis. The specfied field will replace all information on each point except for the value. If no data exists for the specified utype on a particular point the point will be ignored. If no data are found, a SedNoDataException is thrown. If utype is not supported, a SedInconsistentException is thrown.

Parameters:
field - Field
utype - String
Throws:
SedInconsistentException, - SedNoDataException
SedInconsistentException
SedNoDataException

                 throws SedNoDataException,
                        SedInconsistentException
Sets the parameter info of the specified axis. The specfied field will replace all information on each point except for the value. If no data exists for the specified utype on a particular point the point will be ignored. If there are no points to set, a SedNoDataException is thrown. If the utype is not supported a SedInconsistentException is thrown.

Parameters:
